exploratory_workflow.narrative:
3. How many F1 drivers and F1 teams exist in each country?
Get:
wd:Q10841764 --> F1 driver
wdt:P27 --> nationality
Explore for all F1 drivers and their nationality (all F1 driver in the story of F1)
exploratory_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?countryname count(?d) WHERE { ?d wdt:P27 ?country ; wdt:P106 wd:Q10841764 . ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryname . } LIMIT 40
output: United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland
execution_output: United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland

exploratory_workflow.narrative: Now I have to find a way to show the F1 team country
exploratory_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?cname count(?f1t) WHERE { ?f1t wdt:P17 ?c . ?f1t wdt:P31 wd:Q10497835 . ?c <http://schema.org/name> ?cname . } GROUP BY (?cname) LIMIT 40

exploratory_workflow.narrative: Now union of the queries above
exploratory_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?countryname (count(distinct ?d) as ?drivers) (count (distinct ?f1t) as ?f1teams) WHERE { ?d wdt:P106 wd:Q10841764 ; wdt:P27 ?country . OPTIONAL{ ?f1t wdt:P17 ?country ; wdt:P31 wd:Q10497835 . } {SELECT DISTINCT ?country WHERE { ?d wdt:P106 wd:Q10841764 ; wdt:P27 ?country . }} ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryname . } LIMIT 40
output: United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland
execution_output: United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland

exploratory_workflow.narrative:
4. Compare number of F1 drivers to their nationality
4.1 Is there some driver that joined a team in their own country?
Here I find all the F1 drivers who works in a team based in the same country where they were born. I use group_concat
to show all the scuderie for the same person (if exists). All the IRI came from above. (yet explored)
exploratory_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?countryname ?d ?dname (GROUP_CONCAT(DISTINCT ?scuderia ; separator = ", ") AS ?scuderie) ?country_teams WHERE { ?f1t wdt:P17 ?cc ; wdt:P31 wd:Q10497835 . ?d wdt:P106 wd:Q10841764 ; wdt:P54 ?f1t ; wdt:P27 ?c . ?d <http://schema.org/name> ?dname . ?c <http://schema.org/name> ?countryname . ?cc <http://schema.org/name> ?country_teams . ?f1t <http://schema.org/name> ?scuderia . FILTER(?c = ?cc) } LIMIT 40
output: McLaren, Red Bull Racing, Williams Grand Prix Engineering
Andrea Moda Formula, Enzo Coloni Racing Car Systems, Forti
execution_output: McLaren, Red Bull Racing, Williams Grand Prix Engineering
Andrea Moda Formula, Enzo Coloni Racing Car Systems, Forti

exploratory_workflow.narrative:
4.2 Which team employed the larger number of drivers?
Also for this question, I'm going to use IRI found above.
I start by exploring the number of F1 drivers linked to F1 teams
exploratory_workflow.query: SELECT count(?d) WHERE { ?d wdt:P106 wd:Q10841764 ; wdt:P54 ?f1t . ?d <http://schema.org/name> ?dname . } LIMIT 20

exploratory_workflow.narrative: I find the F1 teams and their number of F1 driver in all the story of the Formula Omne
exploratory_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?f1tname (count(?d) AS ?numerodrivers) WHERE { ?d wdt:P106 wd:Q10841764 ; wdt:P54 ?f1t . ?d <http://schema.org/name> ?dname . ?f1t <http://schema.org/name> ?f1tname . } ORDER BY DESC (?numerodrivers) LIMIT 10

exploratory_workflow.narrative:
Now to have the team with max number of drivers, i can use order by descendent and litim to 1 --> to have the team
with max value
exploratory_workflow.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?f1tname (count(?d) AS ?numerodrivers) WHERE { ?d wdt:P106 wd:Q10841764 ; wdt:P54 ?f1t . ?d <http://schema.org/name> ?dname . ?f1t <http://schema.org/name> ?f1tname . } ORDER BY DESC (?numerodrivers) LIMIT 1
